rtened in the curcumin treated model rats. Our study shows that curcumin can significantly improve spatial learning and memory functions in rats with Aβ 1-40 -induced Alzheimer's disease by modulating Bax and Bcl-2 expression.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Wang","given":"Yunliang","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Yunliang","literal":""},{"family":"Yunliang","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Yin","given":"Huaizhi","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Yin","given":"Honglei","literal":""},{"family":"Lou","given":"Jian-Shu","literal":""},{"family":"Honglei","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Lou","given":"Jiyu","literal":""},{"family":"Han","given":"Bing","literal":""},{"family":"Yin","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Han","given":"Bing","literal":""},{"family":"Qin","given":"Xinyue","literal":""},{"family":"Jiyu","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Qin","given":"Xinyue","literal":""},{"family":"Meng","given":"Fanchao","literal":""},{"family":"Lou","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Meng","given":"Fanchao","literal":""},{"family":"Geng","given":"Shuang","literal":""},{"family":"Geng","given":"Shuang","literal":""},{"family":"Liu","given":"Yajun","literal":""},{"family":"Han","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Liu","given":"Yajun","literal":""},{"family":"Xinyue","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Qin","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Fanchao","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Meng","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Shuang","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Geng","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Yajun","given":"","literal":""},{"family":"Liu","given":"","literal":""}],"citation-key":"wang_effects_2011","year":"2011","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Effects of curcumin on hippocampal Bax and Bcl-2 expression and cognitive function of a rat model of Alzheimer's disease"],"author-links":["[[Author/Yunliang Wang]]","[[Author/Yunliang Wang]]","[[Author/Yunliang]]","[[